reviews.text:
The best ever.
Everytime visit here When i travel to HK
Ordered salt& pepper squid, bamboo clams, claypot choy sum and hk stye claypot chicken.  Love it. No regrets.
Good food, were the last customers for the day but still received pretty good service. Had their live seafood so it was a little pricey, but cooking was good!
Much better than the other spicy crab seafood restaurants nearby .... They may be fancier, but this is Mich better value

This is a great 'Dai Pai Dong' spot.  Surrounded by other competitors, this particular spot is the best.  We ordered the affluent shrimp, spicy salt crab, oyster congee, soy sauce noodles, fried chicken, clams, and razor clams.

The seafood was phenomenal. Well cleaned so there was no sand in the shellfish. And it wasn't fishy tasting. Very clean and great taste.

The oyster congee was surprisingly non fishy. The oysters were clean and fresh.

The spicy crab was delicious. The actual crab meat was sweet and cooked perfectly.

The affluent shrimp was tricky to de-shell, but worth the effort.

All in all, a very lively atmosphere and great food. The setting isn't the prettiest or cleanest, but makes for an amazing experience.

reviews.text:
味は美味しいです。値段は昔を知っている日本人から見ると高くなったなぁ、とは思います。星三つにしたのは、この店がそもそも大衆的な店だからで、地元の人がこれだけ多く来ていることから見れば、やはり評判の良い店だと思います。
メニューは写真を見ればいいので言葉が通じなくてもある程度は大丈夫です。魚を食べると高くつくのはどの店も同じですね。

The best ever.
Everytime visit here When i travel to HK
有冷氣嘅高級大排檔。坐得好擠逼。周時坐滿人。菜式，好特別。味道唔差。碟頭好大。不過價錢唔平。食海鮮小心啲。分分鐘俾人劏。以前都冇咁多人。而家多咗好多內地客。價錢當堂貴曬。不過食物質素都保持到，經過可以試下。
Ordered salt& pepper squid, bamboo clams, claypot choy sum and hk stye claypot chicken.  Love it. No regrets.

菜品選擇多
但又貴又鹹
環境吵雜菸味重
